      "variant": "main",
      "html": "<h4>Activity</h4>\n<p>Here are the values of the first 5 terms of 3 sequences:</p>\n<ol type=\"A\">\n  <li>\n    30, 40, 50, 60, 70, . . .\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    0, 5, 15, 30, 50, . . .\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    1, 2, 4, 8, 16, . . .\n  </li>\n</ol>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol>\n      <li>\n        For each sequence, describe a way to produce a new term from the previous term.\n\n        <ol type=\"A\">\n          <li>\n            30, 40, 50, 60, 70, . . .\n          </li>\n        </ol>\n      </li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>Each term is 10 more than the previous term.</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol>\n      <ol start=\"2\" type=\"A\">\n        <li>\n          0, 5, 15, 30, 50, . . .\n        </li>\n      </ol>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>Each term is the result of adding 5 more than was added to the previous term (add 5, then add 10, then add 15).</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol>\n      <ol start=\"3\" type=\"A\">\n        <li>\n          1, 2, 4, 8, 16, . . .\n        </li>\n      </ol>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>Each term is double the previous term.</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol start=\"2\">\n      <li>\n        If the patterns you described continue, which sequence has the second-greatest value for the 10th term?\n\n\n      </li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>Sequence <span>B</span></p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol start=\"3\">\n      <li>\n        Which of these could be geometric sequences? Explain how you know.\n\n\n      </li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>Sequence <span>C</span>. Sample response: A geometric sequence has the same multiplier from one term to the next, the common ratio, and neither A nor B has this. Sequence C does; the common ratio is 2.</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<p>An <span class=\"os-raise-ib-tooltip\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-store=\"glossary-tooltip\">arithmetic sequence</span> is a sequence in which each term is the previous term plus a constant.\n  This constant is called the <span class=\"os-raise-ib-tooltip\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-store=\"glossary-tooltip\">common difference</span>.\n</p>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol start=\"4\">\n      <li>\n        Which of these could be arithmetic sequences? Explain how you know.\n\n\n      </li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>Sequence <span>A</span>. Sample response: An arithmetic sequence gets each term by adding the same constant to the previous term. Sequence A adds 5 to each term to find the next term.\n    </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<h4> Video: Comparing Sequences</h4>\n<p>Watch the following video to learn more about comparing arithmetic and geometric sequences.\n</p>\n<video controls=\"true\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\" width=\"550\">\n  <source src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/509740b91324e860a23860c580fa239d8a51c4dd\">\n  <track default=\"true\" kind=\"captions\" label=\"On\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/12c5ed810194f2f3cdae39856f3db5a28cd0d3c8\" srclang=\"en_us\">https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/509740b91324e860a23860c580fa239d8a51c4dd\n</video>\n<br>\n<br>\n<!-- \"Start \"Are you Ready for More? click to reveal.  If you have more than one on a page, you will need to change the Data-fire/data-wait-for-events for each set.-->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta\" data-button-text=\"Are you ready for more?\" data-fire-event=\"RFM1\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-content\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-prompt\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Start interaction.  If multiple interactions appear under \"are you ready for more?, they should all have matching \"data-wait-for-event\", which should also match the \"data-fire-event\" for the button. Note in this sample, they are all RFM1-->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-wait-for-event=\"RFM1\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <h4>Extending Your Thinking</h4>\n    <p>Elena says that it&rsquo;s not possible to have a sequence of numbers that is both arithmetic and geometric. Do you agree with Elena? Explain your reasoning.</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>Elena is incorrect. Sample explanation: the sequence 1,1,1, . . . is arithmetic (adding 0 each time), but it is also geometric (multiplying by 1 each time).\n    </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--End interaction-->\n<br>"
    }
